<div class="card mt-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">SAML Test Application Privacy Policy</h5>
        <p>
            This SAML Test Application is designed for testing SAML 2.0 integration with Identity Providers.
            It is intended for development and testing purposes only.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Data Collection:</strong> This application collects and displays SAML claims received from
            the Identity Provider during authentication. This data is stored only in the session and is not
            persisted beyond the session lifetime.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Data Usage:</strong> The collected data is used solely for displaying the SAML claims
            received from the Identity Provider and is not shared with any third parties.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Security:</strong> This application implements standard security practices for handling
            SAML authentication. However, as a test application, it may not implement all security best
            practices required for a production environment.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This application is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind,
            either expressed or implied, including, but not limited to, the implied warranties of
            merchantability and fitness for a particular purpose.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
